						               													<description>You play a mob boss who manages a clan and tries to defeat other clans by gathering the most money.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Gangster Paradise, you collect money which you have to launder so that it counts for your score.&amp;#10;On your turn, you will be able to negotiate with your opponents in order to exchange anything you own: money or cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play lasts 8 rounds, divided into 5 phases: each player plays the first phase, then all play a second phase, etc.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During phase 1, each clan collects its own type of goods.&amp;#10;During phase 2, players participate in as many auctions as there are players less one, each collecting 1 good among those offered, the last player receiving money.&amp;#10;During phase 3, players sell their goods, trying to make sets of different goods.&amp;#10;During phase 4, players will hire new gang members, by paying sets of similar goods. Members of different types will trigger special effects during the game.&amp;#10;During phase 5, players first launder their dirty money, collect some extra money and pay their gang members&amp;rsquo; salaries.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When all 8 rounds have been played, laundered money is counted and the winner declared.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
